description:
Join Jader Feij√≥ and Alyssa Truman in this episode of ANN In-Depth as they discuss technology and innovation within the Adventist Church.

As an expert in innovation and technology, Feij√≥ shares his insights on how the Church can create an innovation arm to feed back into the whole organization. He also explores the possibilities of artificial intelligence and its impact on evangelism and the Church‚Äôs mission. Tune in for a thought-provoking conversation on revolutionizing old institutions and adapting to new technologies. 

The Seventh-day Adventist Church has been an established denomination since 1863. It is a global Christian family with over 21 million members who hold the Bible as the ultimate authority. We are believers who promise to help people understand the Bible to find freedom, healing, and hope in Jesus.
